postcontent:
This is a Romanian SAR-3 AK-47/AKM style variant semi-automatic assault rifle that is chambered in 5.56 x 45mm (.223 Remington) caliber and that was built in limited numbers during the Clinton Assault Weapon Ban. This particular gun was made by S.N. ROMARM SA/CUGIR in Romania and imported by C.A.I., ST. ALB, VT. By the serial number it appears this weapon was built in the year 2000 and has been shot very little over the years since I purchased this weapon around that time. It has a 16" barrel with no muzzle brake or threading on the barrel with a side mount v-rail for scope attachment. It comes with a MTK-83 attachable side mount scope rail made in Belarus with a black    3x9x42mm objective NcStar brand short length scope with a sniper style recticle and the mount can be removed/attached without losing zero from the gun. This mount also allows use of the regular iron sights when it is attached to the gun since it is a cantilever style curved mount. It also includes see-thru scope covers on bungee type cords that can be removed or left on during shooting.
It also comes with 5 - .223 caliber marked Bakelite tan colored 30 - round magazines, 1 - black polymer circle 10 marked - 5.56x45mm 30 - round magazine, and 1 - blued steel 5.56x45mm 5 - round magazine that came with the gun which has no markings. It also has a very nice heavy 1-1/2" nylon adjustable strap that was on the gun when I purchased it all those years ago. The weapon comes with a Doskosport brand hard plastic case which is 52" long x 15' wide with a carry handle. It has 4 closure latches and gray egg shell foam in the top/bottom of the case to protect the weapon. The fit/finish on the weapon is in very good condition and the safety has never been engaged which usually marks the side of the receiver. I purchased the weapon new about 14 years ago from Bill's Gun Shop in Robbinsdale, MN and I have not fired the gun very much all these years. I am looking to sell this gun for cash and I am not looking to make any trades at this point. Beretta Bobcat: Defining the Pocket Pistol

Comparable in size to a smart phone and weighing only 11.5 oz, the ultra-concealable Bobcat has been the ultimate pocket pistol for over three decades.

It is user-friendly, durable, reliable and accurate, while with its snag-free lines is can be tucked in any kind of holster or pocket for deep concealment. It is perfect for concealed carry (on its own or as a backup pistol), and it keeps besting all pistols in its class for quality, value and design.   

User-friendly design is common to all Beretta small frames. The exclusive tip-up barrel allows the user to easily load a round directly into the chamber without racking the slide. It also assists in the safe clearing of the pistol by giving an easy and absolutely safe way to check the bore and and remove a live cartridge. Jamming and stove-piping problems are virtually eliminated by the open slide design shared by all small frame Berettas.

Beretta pistols in the 21 Series utilize a tough forging process for their barrels, while slides are fashioned from solid steel bar stock--and frames from solid aluminum forgings. The new stainless-steel version (“Inox”) employs the finest and toughest steels, making it exceptionally corrosion resistant and durable.
